### Direct Backend Endpoint Tests - Baseline Validation
### 
### This test collection validates AI service backends directly (bypassing APIM) to establish
### baseline functionality and performance for comparison against the unified gateway behavior.
### 
### Prerequisites (see ReadMe for details):
### 1. Run `azd up` to provision the infrastructure and create the VS Code settings file with all required variables
### 2. Ensure your APIM instance and backends are successfully deployed
###
### Test Coverage:
### - Microsoft Foundry direct endpoint validation
### - Google Gemini direct API endpoint validation  
###
### Usage:
### - Click "Send Request" above each request in VS Code with REST Client extension
### - All required variables are automatically extracted from VS Code settings file generated by `azd up`
### - Compare responses with unified gateway tests to validate routing behavior

# API Version Constants (not variables - these are static values)
@gptApiVersion = 2025-01-01-preview
@foundryApiVersion = 2024-05-01-preview

# GPT-4o endpoints (region1 primary)
@premiumEndpoint = {{foundry_premium_region1_endpoint}}

# GPT-4.1-mini endpoints (region1 primary) 
@standardEndpoint = {{foundry_standard_region1_endpoint}}

# Phi-4 model endpoint
@inferenceEndpoint = {{foundry_inference_endpoint}}

# Google Gemini endpoint
@geminiEndpoint = {{gemini_endpoint}}

###############################################################################
### Microsoft Foundry Direct Endpoint Tests
###############################################################################

### Test: Phi-4 Direct Call (Baseline)
POST {{inferenceEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/phi-4/chat/completions?api-version={{foundryApiVersion}}
api-key: {{foundry_inference_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "phi-4",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I am going to Paris, what should I see?"
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 100,
  "temperature": 0.8,
  "top_p": 0.1,
  "presence_penalty": 0,
  "frequency_penalty": 0
}

### Test: GPT-4.1 Direct Call (Baseline)
POST {{premiumEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4.1/chat/completions?api-version={{gptApiVersion}}
api-key: {{foundry_premium_region1_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4.1",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful AI assistant."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hello! This is a test of the GPT-4.1 backend directly. Can you confirm you received this message by returning a random song verse?"
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 100,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

### Test: GPT-4.1-mini Direct Call (Baseline)
POST {{standardEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4.1-mini/chat/completions?api-version={{gptApiVersion}}
api-key: {{foundry_standard_region1_key}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4.1-mini",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "system",
      "content": "You are a helpful AI assistant."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hello! This is a test of the GPT-4.1-mini backend directly. Can you confirm you received this messageby citing a poem verse?"
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 100,
  "temperature": 0.7
}

###############################################################################
### Google Gemini Direct Endpoint Tests
###############################################################################

### Test: Google Gemini Direct Call (Baseline)
POST {{geminiEndpoint}}/v1beta/openai/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{gemini_api_key}}

{
    "model": "gemini-2.5-flash-lite",
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "system",
            "content": "You are a helpful AI assistant."
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Hello! This is a test of the Gemini OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint. Can you confirm you received this message?"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 100,
    "temperature": 0.7
}

###